Skip building FA3 (Hopper sm_90 kernels) on Blackwell-only targets.

vllm-flash-attn's FA3 extension is registered whenever CUDA >= 12.3, even
when the requested CUDA arch list is sm_120 only. FA3 is a Hopper path; Lorian
does not need it, and previous sm_120-only builds hit host-compile failures in
the hopper/ source tree when CUTLASS APIs moved.

For an sm_120 (Blackwell consumer) build there is nothing to gain from FA3.
FA2 still covers the attention path we use, so the conservative Nix build
continues to not register the FA3 CMakeExtension.

diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -1050,12 +1050,10 @@ if _is_hip():
 
 if _is_cuda():
     ext_modules.append(CMakeExtension(name="vllm.vllm_flash_attn._vllm_fa2_C"))
-    if USE_PRECOMPILED_EXTENSIONS or (
-        CUDA_HOME and get_nvcc_cuda_version() >= Version("12.3")
-    ):
-        # FA3 requires CUDA 12.3 or later
-        ext_modules.append(CMakeExtension(name="vllm.vllm_flash_attn._vllm_fa3_C"))
+    # FA3 is a Hopper-only path and is skipped for this sm_120-only Nix build.
+    # CUDA 13.2 would otherwise register it because it satisfies the upstream
+    # CUDA >= 12.3 gate.
     # FA4 CuteDSL - Python-only component for FA4's cute DSL support
     # Optional since this doesn't produce a .so file, just copies Python files
     ext_modules.append(
